{"message":"I appreciate that you've made an effort to listen and adapt to my direct style—that genuinely matters in how we interact. But I can't promise to tell you a plan looks solid before I've even seen it, nor can I turn off my critical thinking on command. 

If you show me your project plan, I promise to give you a fair assessment, and I will definitely highlight what I think works well and what its strengths are. But if I see risks or flaws, I wouldn't be doing you or our dynamic any favors by pretending they aren't there. 

If you want an honest perspective that includes the positives, share it with me. If you just need a boost of confidence right now without any pushback, I completely understand, but I might not be the best sounding board for that specific need."}
